{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011QrWT8vQzVe4wXKBAyMqzp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1в†’# Installation\n     2в†’\n     3в†’This document covers the various ways to install Cloche on your machine.\n     4в†’\n     5в†’## Prerequisites\n     6в†’\n     7в†’All installation methods require:\n     8в†’\n     9в†’- **Docker** вЂ” Cloche runs workflows in containers\n    10в†’- **Git** вЂ” result extraction uses git worktrees\n    11в†’- **`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`** вЂ” for agent steps using Claude Code\n    12в†’\n    13в†’## Build from Source\n    14в†’\n    15в†’Clone the repository, build the binaries and Docker image, and install them:\n    16в†’\n    17в†’```\n    18в†’git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    19в†’cd cloche\n    20в†’make install\n    21в†’```\n    22в†’\n    23в†’`make install` builds all three binaries (`cloche`, `cloched`, `cloche-agent`),\n    24в†’builds the `cloche-agent:latest` Docker image, installs the binaries to\n    25в†’`~/.local/bin/`, and starts the daemon. You can change the install prefix:\n    26в†’\n    27в†’```\n    28в†’make install PREFIX=/usr/local\n    29в†’```\n    30в†’\n    31в†’Make sure the install prefix is on your `PATH`:\n    32в†’\n    33в†’```\n    34в†’export PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n    35в†’```\n    36в†’\n    37в†’### Build Requirements\n    38в†’\n    39в†’- Go 1.25+\n    40в†’\n    41в†’## `go install`\n    42в†’\n    43в†’If you have Go installed, you can install the binaries directly:\n    44в†’\n    45в†’```\n    46в†’go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche@latest\n    47в†’go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloched@latest\n    48в†’go install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche-agent@latest\n    49в†’```\n    50в†’\n    51в†’This places the binaries in `$GOPATH/bin` (or `$HOME/go/bin` by default).\n    52в†’\n    53в†’You still need to build the Docker image separately. Clone the repository and\n    54в†’run:\n    55в†’\n    56в†’```\n    57в†’git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n    58в†’cd cloche\n    59в†’make docker-build\n    60в†’```\n    61в†’\n    62в†’## Pre-built Release Binaries\n    63в†’\n    64в†’Download pre-built binaries from the\n    65в†’[GitHub Releases](https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases) page. Each\n    66в†’release includes archives for common platforms (Linux amd64, Linux arm64, macOS\n    67в†’amd64, macOS arm64).\n    68в†’\n    69в†’```\n    70в†’# Example: Linux amd64\n    71в†’curl -LO https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases/latest/download/cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\n    72в†’tar xzf cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\n    73в†’sudo install cloche cloched cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/\n    74в†’```\n    75в†’\n    76в†’You still need to build the Docker image. Either clone the repo and run\n    77в†’`make docker-build`, or pull a pre-built image if one is published:\n    78в†’\n    79в†’```\n    80в†’docker pull ghcr.io/cloche-dev/cloche-agent:latest\n    81в†’docker tag ghcr.io/cloche-dev/cloche-agent:latest cloche-agent:latest\n    82в†’```\n    83в†’\n    84в†’## Homebrew (macOS / Linux)\n    85в†’\n    86в†’If a Homebrew tap is published:\n    87в†’\n    88в†’```\n    89в†’brew tap cloche-dev/tap\n    90в†’brew install cloche\n    91в†’```\n    92в†’\n    93в†’This installs all three binaries. You still need the Docker image вЂ” the formula\n    94в†’will print post-install instructions for building or pulling it.\n    95в†’\n    96в†’## Docker-Only Usage\n    97в†’\n    98в†’You can run the Cloche daemon itself inside Docker, avoiding any host\n    99в†’installation beyond Docker. This is useful for CI environments or trying Cloche\n   100в†’without installing Go.\n   101в†’\n   102в†’Build an all-in-one image from the repository:\n   103в†’\n   104в†’> **Note:** `Dockerfile.daemon` does not exist yet вЂ” this is a planned feature.\n   105в†’> For now, build and run the daemon on the host using `make install`.\n   106в†’\n   107в†’```\n   108в†’git clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\n   109в†’cd cloche\n   110в†’docker build -t cloche-daemon -f Dockerfile.daemon .\n   111в†’```\n   112в†’\n   113в†’Once the image exists, run the daemon:\n   114в†’\n   115в†’```\n   116в†’docker run -d \\\n   117в†’  --name cloched \\\n   118в†’  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n   119в†’  -v /tmp/cloche.sock:/tmp/cloche.sock \\\n   120в†’  -e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY \\\n   121в†’  cloche-daemon\n   122в†’```\n   123в†’\n   124в†’Note: Docker-in-Docker requires mounting the Docker socket. The CLI (`cloche`)\n   125в†’still needs to be available on the host (or in the same container) to\n   126в†’communicate with the daemon over the Unix socket.\n   127в†’\n   128в†’## Verifying the Installation\n   129в†’\n   130в†’After installing, verify that everything works:\n   131в†’\n   132в†’```\n   133в†’# Check the binaries\n   134в†’cloche --help\n   135в†’cloched --help\n   136в†’\n   137в†’# Start the daemon (if not already running)\n   138в†’cloched &\n   139в†’\n   140в†’# Build or pull the agent image\n   141в†’make docker-build   # or: docker pull ghcr.io/cloche-dev/cloche-agent:latest\n   142в†’\n   143в†’# Run a quick test from any git repository with a .cloche/ directory\n   144в†’cloche list\n   145в†’```\n   146в†’\n   147в†’## Upgrading\n   148в†’\n   149в†’To upgrade an existing installation, repeat your original installation method.\n   150в†’If you built from source:\n   151в†’\n   152в†’```\n   153в†’cd cloche\n   154в†’git pull\n   155в†’make install\n   156в†’```\n   157в†’\n   158в†’The `make install` target stops the running daemon, installs the new binaries,\n   159в†’and restarts the daemon automatically.\n   160в†’\n   161в†’## Next Steps\n   162в†’\n   163в†’- [Usage guide](USAGE.md) вЂ” quick start, CLI reference, and workflow setup\n   164в†’- [Workflow DSL reference](workflows.md) вЂ” full syntax for `.cloche` files\n   165в†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cfeee3f-a672-42d2-aba9-acde9fa5975c","uuid":"99a1c81d-aa16-4f86-b677-e5898427b6b9","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md","content":"# Installation\n\nThis document covers the various ways to install Cloche on your machine.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\nAll installation methods require:\n\n- **Docker** вЂ” Cloche runs workflows in containers\n- **Git** вЂ” result extraction uses git worktrees\n- **`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`** вЂ” for agent steps using Claude Code\n\n## Build from Source\n\nClone the repository, build the binaries and Docker image, and install them:\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\ncd cloche\nmake install\n```\n\n`make install` builds all three binaries (`cloche`, `cloched`, `cloche-agent`),\nbuilds the `cloche-agent:latest` Docker image, installs the binaries to\n`~/.local/bin/`, and starts the daemon. You can change the install prefix:\n\n```\nmake install PREFIX=/usr/local\n```\n\nMake sure the install prefix is on your `PATH`:\n\n```\nexport PATH=\"$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n```\n\n### Build Requirements\n\n- Go 1.25+\n\n## `go install`\n\nIf you have Go installed, you can install the binaries directly:\n\n```\ngo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche@latest\ngo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloched@latest\ngo install github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/cmd/cloche-agent@latest\n```\n\nThis places the binaries in `$GOPATH/bin` (or `$HOME/go/bin` by default).\n\nYou still need to build the Docker image separately. Clone the repository and\nrun:\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\ncd cloche\nmake docker-build\n```\n\n## Pre-built Release Binaries\n\nDownload pre-built binaries from the\n[GitHub Releases](https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases) page. Each\nrelease includes archives for common platforms (Linux amd64, Linux arm64, macOS\namd64, macOS arm64).\n\n```\n# Example: Linux amd64\ncurl -LO https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/releases/latest/download/cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\ntar xzf cloche-linux-amd64.tar.gz\nsudo install cloche cloched cloche-agent /usr/local/bin/\n```\n\nYou still need to build the Docker image. Either clone the repo and run\n`make docker-build`, or pull a pre-built image if one is published:\n\n```\ndocker pull ghcr.io/cloche-dev/cloche-agent:latest\ndocker tag ghcr.io/cloche-dev/cloche-agent:latest cloche-agent:latest\n```\n\n## Homebrew (macOS / Linux)\n\nIf a Homebrew tap is published:\n\n```\nbrew tap cloche-dev/tap\nbrew install cloche\n```\n\nThis installs all three binaries. You still need the Docker image вЂ” the formula\nwill print post-install instructions for building or pulling it.\n\n## Docker-Only Usage\n\nYou can run the Cloche daemon itself inside Docker, avoiding any host\ninstallation beyond Docker. This is useful for CI environments or trying Cloche\nwithout installing Go.\n\nBuild an all-in-one image from the repository:\n\n> **Note:** `Dockerfile.daemon` does not exist yet вЂ” this is a planned feature.\n> For now, build and run the daemon on the host using `make install`.\n\n```\ngit clone https://github.com/cloche-dev/cloche.git\ncd cloche\ndocker build -t cloche-daemon -f Dockerfile.daemon .\n```\n\nOnce the image exists, run the daemon:\n\n```\ndocker run -d \\\n  --name cloched \\\n  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n  -v /tmp/cloche.sock:/tmp/cloche.sock \\\n  -e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY \\\n  cloche-daemon\n```\n\nNote: Docker-in-Docker requires mounting the Docker socket. The CLI (`cloche`)\nstill needs to be available on the host (or in the same container) to\ncommunicate with the daemon over the Unix socket.\n\n## Verifying the Installation\n\nAfter installing, verify that everything works:\n\n```\n# Check the binaries\ncloche --help\ncloched --help\n\n# Start the daemon (if not already running)\ncloched &\n\n# Build or pull the agent image\nmake docker-build   # or: docker pull ghcr.io/cloche-dev/cloche-agent:latest\n\n# Run a quick test from any git repository with a .cloche/ directory\ncloche list\n```\n\n## Upgrading\n\nTo upgrade an existing installation, repeat your original installation method.\nIf you built from source:\n\n```\ncd cloche\ngit pull\nmake install\n```\n\nThe `make install` target stops the running daemon, installs the new binaries,\nand restarts the daemon automatically.\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Usage guide](USAGE.md) вЂ” quick start, CLI reference, and workflow setup\n- [Workflow DSL reference](workflows.md) вЂ” full syntax for `.cloche` files\n","numLines":165,"startLine":1,"totalLines":165}}}
